com.misc.common.moplaf.solver

Interface Generator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GeneratorImpl

    public interface Generator
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'Generator'.

    A Generator is a problem formulation (linear, constraints, ...), containing variables (GeneratorVar) and constraints (GeneratorCons).

    SolutionProviders (typically, solvers) will produce Solutions for this problem formulation.

    A Generator is structured as follows:

    • a Generator is a set of trees (a fores) of tuples: GeneratorTuple
    • a Generator has GeneratorTuple roots
    • a GeneratorTuple has GeneratorTuple elements (children) and possibly a GeneratorTuple container (parent)
    • a GeneratorTuple, has : GeneratorTupleMember members
    • there are two kinds of GeneratorTupleMembers
      • variables: GeneratorVar
      • constraints: GeneratorCons

    A generator provides

    • a helper allowing to traverse all the tuples: interface ITupleVisitor and method visitTuples(ITupleVisitor)
    • helpers to construct itself: methods generateTuples() and generateRootTuples()
    • helpers to construct the variables and the constraints: methods generateVars() and generateCons()

    A generator may select one solution among its pool of solutions: setSelected(Solution). The selected solution is used to show properties of this Generator elements for the selected solution.

    The following features are supported:

    • Tuple Root
    • Generator Feature Modes
    • Remarks
    • Footprint Nof Vars
    • Footprint Nof Cons
    • Footprint Nof Terms
    • Count Cons
    • Count Vars
    • ELp Var Count
    • ELp Cons Count
    • Code
    • Solution Provider
    • Selected
    • Goals
    See Also:
    SolverPackage.getGenerator()
